In this memorandum, President Joseph R. Biden Jr. delegates the functions and authorities of Section 1299F(i) of the William M. (Mac) Thornberry National Defense Authorization Act for Fiscal Year 2021 to the Secretary of State. The President's authority to make this delegation is derived from the Constitution and the laws of the United States, specifically section 301 of title 3, United States Code. The memorandum also instructs the Secretary of State to publish the memorandum in the Federal Register.